FBIS4-53564 "dreas098_a_94019" FBIS-EAS-94-098 Daily Report 20 May 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Reports Concerning Public Utility Rate Continue Reports Concerning Public Utility Rate Continue Minister Seeks System Reform OW2005025594 Tokyo KYODO in English 0241 GMT 20 May 94 OW2005025594 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, may 20 KYODO -- Agriculture Minister Mutsuki Kato called Friday [20 May] for an overhaul of the present system of calculation for public service rates. Kato made the remark after Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata's government endorsed a freeze on public service charges until the end of the year. It is necessary to make a thorough review of the calculation system rather than merely postpone rate hikes, he said.
